import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of size in the dataset?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_size_by_name = data.groupby('name')['size'].mean()
    avg_size_by_name.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average size of the items in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['parent'] = data['parent'].astype(str)
    data.boxplot(column='size', by='parent', grid=False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45 if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20 else 0)
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("What is the size distribution of items by their parent?")
    plt.suptitle("")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data.plot(kind='density', x='name', y='size')
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Size')
    plt.title('What is the size distribution of items by their name?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
